quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  11,25,"And assuredly We sent Nuh unto his people saying: verily I am unto you a plain warner"
  11,26,That ye shall worship none except Allah; verily I fear for you the torment of a Day afflictive
  11,27,"The chiefs of those who disbelieved among his people said: we behold thee except as a human being like us, and we behold not any follow thee except the meanest of us, by an immature opinion; nor We behold in you any exellency over us; nay! we deem you liars"
  11,28,"He said: bethink ye, O my people! if I rested upon an evidence from my Lord, and a mercy hath come unto me from Him, and that hath been obscured unto you, Shall we make you adhere to it while ye are averse thereto"
  11,29,"And, O my people, I ask not of you any riches therefor; my hire is not but with Allah. And I am not going to drive away those who have believed; verily they are going to meet their Lord; but I behold you a people ignorant"
  11,30,"O My people! who will succour me against Allah, if I drave them away! Admonished are ye not then"
  11,31,"And I say not unto you that with me are the treasures of Allah, nor that I know the Unseen; nor I say, I am an angel. And say not of those whom your eyes condemn that Allah shall not bestow on them good - -Allah knoweth best that which is in theeir souls. Verily in that case would be of the wrong-doers"
  11,32,"They said: O Nuh! surely thou hast disputed with us and hath multiplied the disputation with us; now bring us that wherewith thou threatenest us, if thou be of the truth-tellers"
  11,33,"He said: only Allah will bring it on you if He will, and ye shall not escape"
  11,34,"Nor would my good counsel profit you, even though I wished to give you good counsel, if Allah willed to keep you astray. He is your Lord, and unto Him ye shall be returned"
  11,35,"Or say they: he hath fabricated it? Say thou: on me then be my guilt, and I am quit of that whereof ye are guilty"